From da97fbb915700293350f3c324028ac7399b71b34 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 15:08:53 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 039/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20hppa32/hppa64/riscv32=20PAGE=5F?=
 =?UTF-8?q?MMUSHIFT=3D4=20boot=20=E2=80=94=2015/15=20pgcl-test=20+=208/8?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20pgcl-stress=20PASS?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PA-RISC (hppa32 + hppa64):
- Page table geometry: PLD_SHIFT=MMUPAGE_SHIFT (4KB hardware pages), giving
  1024 PTEs per MMUPAGE-sized table. BITS_PER_PTE, BITS_PER_PMD, BITS_PER_PGD
  all derive from MMUPAGE_SHIFT.
- inventory.c pagezero_memconfig: PDC firmware reports memory in bytes;
  set_pmem_entry expects 4KB page count. Was converting bytes>>PAGE_SHIFT
  (kernel pages), causing double conversion (512MB→32MB). Fix: MMUPAGE_SHIFT.
- entry.S TLB miss handler: PTE table index extraction and offset clearing
  use ASM_PLD_SHIFT (=MMUPAGE_SHIFT) instead of PAGE_SHIFT.
- head.S early page table setup: PGD stride and PFN calculations use
  MMUPAGE_SIZE/MMUPAGE_SHIFT for 4KB hardware page granularity.
- pgtable.h PTE encoding: pfn_pte/pte_pfn use PAGE_SHIFT (PAGE-granular PFN).
  set_ptes PGCL loop writes PAGE_MMUCOUNT sub-page PTEs per kernel page.
  PAGE_ADD_SHIFT=0 (PTE already stores 4KB-granular physical address).
- fixmap.h: FIXMAP_SIZE and __fix_to_virt use MMUPAGE_SHIFT (hardware pages).
- init.c map_pages: PTE index, address stride use MMUPAGE granularity.
  Gateway page mapping uses MMUPAGE_MASK/MMUPAGE_SIZE.
- sys_parisc.c: 9 MMUPAGE fixes for mmap alignment, color alignment,
  stack randomization, shared memory offset calculations.
- shmparam.h: SHMLBA=MMUPAGE_SIZE (hardware cache alias granularity).
- cache.c flush_kernel_dcache_range_asm: MMUPAGE_SIZE stride.

RISC-V 32-bit:
- pgtable.h FIXADDR_TOP: PGDIR-aligned on rv32 so FDT early mapping via
  PGDIR_SIZE superpages calculates dtb_early_va correctly.
- patch.c text patching: Use page_to_phys() instead of __pa() for vmalloc
  addresses; chunk size MMUPAGE_SIZE for fixmap granularity.

Generic:
- pgtable.h: Move __phys_to_pte_val default before set_ptes (no functional
  change, allows arch-specific set_ptes to reference it).

Tested: hppa32 (QEMU B160L, nosmp), hppa64 (QEMU C3700, SMP=4, 32-bit
compat), riscv32 (QEMU virt, SMP=4). All 23/23 PASS, zero kernel warnings.
13 architectures now boot with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
